<dl id="n53093c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53093c">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53093c"> 93(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Lot, br of A, K Norway</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Lot, his sister&apos;s husband</mark>, is given what was his of ancestral right, the <mark>crown of Norway</mark>, just at the time, as we are told incidentally, when &ldquo;Gawain, the son of Lot, was a youth of twelve years, and had been sent by his uncle to be brought up as a page in the service of Pope Sulpicius.&rdquo; <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA3"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 77f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
